The paper discusses a visual place recognition algorithm for navigating robots, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The algorithm uses computer vision techniques to recognise places under changing environmental conditions, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses parameter tuning and characterisation, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the application of the algorithm to robotic systems suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
